        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Estimated value. Value of production quantity (m3) is retrieved from EuroStat for the year 2016, accessed on 20231010. Production quantity is 60'377'265 m3, multiplied by the average brick bulk density of 1.6 kg/dm3.

Reference production quantity: "Non-refractory clay building bricks (excluding of siliceous fossil meals or earths)", EUROPEAN UNION (28), PRODQNT.
Industry, trade and services&gt;Statistics on the production of manufactured foods (prom)&gt;Sold production, exports and imports (ds-056120). Retrieved from: https://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/databrowser/view/DS-056120__custom_7766536/default/table?lang=en

Reference brick bulk density: v2 Report 7, Buildings, Part IV, p. 9. For hollow bricks there are requirements for compression strength (4 - 28 MPa) and brick bulk density of 1.0 -2.2 kg/dm3. (The brick bulk density is calculated by dividing the mass of the dried brick by its volume including all channels, finger holes, and mortar pockets, or frogs.) 

</productionVolumeComment>
